headlines.shortLinkText: Shorthanded Syracuse hands Louisville third straight loss

headlines.description: Juwan Morgan had 24 points and eight rebounds and Robert Johnson scored 19 points to lead Indiana past Rutgers 65-43 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morgan scores 24, Johnson adds 19 as Indiana beats Rutgers

headlines.description: Tyler Nelson hit four 3-pointers and finished with 27 points and Ferron Flavors Jr. scored 13 of his 16 points in the second half to help Fairfield beat Siena 78-65 on Monday night for its third win in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nelson, Flavors hit 4 3s each; Fairfield beats Siena 78-65

headlines.description: Pat Andree had 24 points, Jordan Cohen added a career-high 21 and Lehigh snapped Bucknell's 10-game win streak 92-89 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lehigh snaps Bucknell's 10-game winning streak 92-89 in OT

headlines.description: Jermaine Marrow had 25 points, nine rebounds and eight assists, Kalin Fisher added 16 points and Hampton led wire-to-wire in beating North Carolina Central 86-70 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marrow scores 25, Hampton beats NC Central 86-70

headlines.description: Kameron Langley and Femi Olujobi each scored 11 points and North Carolina A&T held off Delaware State 54-51 on Monday for its eighth win in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC A&T holds off upset-minded Delaware St. 54-51

headlines.description: Tiwian Kendley scored 27 points and Phillip Carr had his 12th double-double of the season to help Morgan State beat Howard 97-61 on Monday night and snap a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kendley, Carr help Morgan State cruise past Howard, 97-61

headlines.description: Preston Bungei had 20 points and 11 rebounds, Kyle Williams added 16 points with four 3-pointers and Norfolk State beat Bethune-Cookman 83-79 on Monday night.
Logan McIntosh scored 13 points Monday night and hit two free throws with 6.4 seconds left to help Maryland-Eastern Shore end a seven-game skid 62-61 over Florida A&M.
headlines.shortLinkText: UMES ends 7-game skid, beats Florida A&M 62-61

headlines.description: Lamar Morgan hit four 3-pointers and finished with 16 points and Lucian Brownlee scored 15 points to help Coppin State beat South Carolina State 84-60 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morgan hits 4 3s, scores 16 as Coppin State beats SC State

headlines.description: Fausto Pichardo scored a career-high 17 points and grabbed 15 rebounds to help Alabama State upset Southwestern Athletic Conference leader Arkansas-Pine Bluff 65-59 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alabama St. knocks off SWAC leader Arkansas-Pine Bluff 65-59

headlines.description: Jordan Evans had 23 points on Monday night and Mississippi Valley State overcame a 13-point, first-half deficit to beat Alabama A&M 77-67.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mississippi Valley State beats Alabama A&M 77-67

headlines.description: Shirmane Thomas hit three 3-pointers and finished with 21 points and Ivy Smith Jr. had 20 points, nine rebounds and six assists to help Grambling State beat Alcorn State 81-72 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas, Smith help Grambling State beat Alcorn State 81-72

headlines.description: Jared Sam had 18 points and 13 rebounds, Eddie Reese made a pair of free throws with 10.7 seconds left and Southern held on 67-62 over Jackson State on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southern holds on for 67-62 win over Jackson State

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
